# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: UnionKingdom | Scene: UnionKingdom11
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "When Sarah arrived at the council room, she quickly found her seat."
    new "When Sarah arrived at the council room, she quickly found her seat."

    old "Looking about the room, she realized she had begun to feel familiar with it."
    new "Looking about the room, she realized she had begun to feel familiar with it."

    old "She wished she never would."
    new "She wished she never would."

    old "This was no home."
    new "This was no home."

    old "She had to remind herself of the dangers that this place posed. Even behind the smiling faces."
    new "She had to remind herself of the dangers that this place posed. Even behind the smiling faces."

    old "Next to her, she saw Maeiv smiling at her. Just one such face."
    new "Next to her, she saw Maeiv smiling at her. Just one such face."

    old "We gather again to settle the second matter of our council."
    new "We gather again to settle the second matter of our council."

    old "The matter of enshrining the political rights of our subject in a single, unified document for the entire Union."
    new "The matter of enshrining the political rights of our subject in a single, unified document for the entire Union."

    old "The others all nodded."
    new "The others all nodded."

    old "Though the details remain many and varied, with which I will not bore all of you, we must however still settle on the broad points."
    new "Though the details remain many and varied, with which I will not bore all of you, we must however still settle on the broad points."

    old "In particular..."
    new "In particular..."

    old "Shall we find in favor of the nobility or the commoners, when formulating this new document?"
    new "Shall we find in favor of the nobility or the commoners, when formulating this new document?"

    old "Maeiv placed the box on the table."
    new "Maeiv placed the box on the table."

    old "As before, we shall cast and count the votes."
    new "As before, we shall cast and count the votes."

    old "Please, proceed."
    new "Please, proceed."

    old "Just as before, each submitted their votes."
    new "Just as before, each submitted their votes."

    old "Just as before, Maeiv opened the box and began to count them."
    new "Just as before, Maeiv opened the box and began to count them."

    old "[supportcommoners] votes cast in favor of siding with the commoners."
    new "[supportcommoners] votes cast in favor of siding with the commoners."

    old "The majority supports the position standing with the commoners."
    new "The majority supports the position standing with the commoners."

    old "By decision of this council, we shall work to draft a document, protecting their political rights."
    new "By decision of this council, we shall work to draft a document, protecting their political rights."

    old "She had managed to secure her victory by securing the votes for her position."
    new "She had managed to secure her victory by securing the votes for her position."

    old "Sarah realized she had failed to secure the support for her position."
    new "Sarah realized she had failed to secure the support for her position."

    old "This was a painful defeat."
    new "This was a painful defeat."

    old "[supportnobles] votes cast in favor of siding with the nobility."
    new "[supportnobles] votes cast in favor of siding with the nobility."

    old "There is a majority support for the position."
    new "There is a majority support for the position."

    old "The motion passes."
    new "The motion passes."

    old "By decision of this council, we shall work to draft a document, protecting the political rights of the nobility."
    new "By decision of this council, we shall work to draft a document, protecting the political rights of the nobility."

    old "Sarah had managed to secure her victory on the matter."
    new "Sarah had managed to secure her victory on the matter."

    old "She had failed to secure the support for her position."
    new "She had failed to secure the support for her position."

    old "Maeiv dropped the voting papers on the table."
    new "Maeiv dropped the voting papers on the table."

    old "Once they had meant everything. Now that the vote had passed, they were simply paper again."
    new "Once they had meant everything. Now that the vote had passed, they were simply paper again."

    old "We have passed our votes, now we must see to the work that is to be done."
    new "We have passed our votes, now we must see to the work that is to be done."

    old "We shall reconvene soon enough."
    new "We shall reconvene soon enough."

    old "Maeiv stood up and almost turned to leave."
    new "Maeiv stood up and almost turned to leave."

    old "Wait!"
    new "Wait!"

    old "Maeiv looked at Sarah."
    new "Maeiv looked at Sarah."

    old "You failed to speak to the matter of the next council."
    new "You failed to speak to the matter of the next council."

    old "Aah, of course my dear. I am so busy, I sometimes imagine I will forget my own head."
    new "Aah, of course my dear. I am so busy, I sometimes imagine I will forget my own head."

    old "Maeiv looked around the room."
    new "Maeiv looked around the room."

    old "In the next session, we shall settle the most important matter of all."
    new "In the next session, we shall settle the most important matter of all."

    old "Sarah could see the others, even the otherwise uninterested Antonio, lean in."
    new "Sarah could see the others, even the otherwise uninterested Antonio, lean in."

    old "At the next session, we shall determine who will take on the seat at the head of this Union."
    new "At the next session, we shall determine who will take on the seat at the head of this Union."

    old "Maeiv turned and left, leaving the room in stunned silence."
    new "Maeiv turned and left, leaving the room in stunned silence."

    old "Those that remained all eyed one another."
    new "Those that remained all eyed one another."

    old "Before they had been peers, but now there was a proposal for one of them to rise further still."
    new "Before they had been peers, but now there was a proposal for one of them to rise further still."

    old "First among equals."
    new "First among equals."

    old "None spoke, each retreating to their private rooms."
    new "None spoke, each retreating to their private rooms."

    old "When Sarah arrived back at her room, she took her seat at her desk again."
    new "When Sarah arrived back at her room, she took her seat at her desk again."

    old "Papers strewed about, piling up documents."
    new "Papers strewed about, piling up documents."

    old "It had all seemd so utterly important, and now it was all dwarfed by the latest proposal."
    new "It had all seemd so utterly important, and now it was all dwarfed by the latest proposal."

    old "A leader for the whole of the Union."
    new "A leader for the whole of the Union."

    old "A Union King."
    new "A Union King."

    old "Or Queen, Sarah thought to herself."
    new "Or Queen, Sarah thought to herself."

    old "In the silence of the room, she was able to consider and reflect."
    new "In the silence of the room, she was able to consider and reflect."

    old "It wasn't long before Sarah realized that perhaps all of this had been foreplay."
    new "It wasn't long before Sarah realized that perhaps all of this had been foreplay."

    old "That the one true ambition of Maeiv had been this last and final proposal."
    new "That the one true ambition of Maeiv had been this last and final proposal."

    old "To seize something through politicking which she could not win by force."
    new "To seize something through politicking which she could not win by force."

    old "It had been centuries since the Union had last seen a single leader."
    new "It had been centuries since the Union had last seen a single leader."

    old "Still, despite the ages passed, there was a tradition for it. It was not unthinkable."
    new "Still, despite the ages passed, there was a tradition for it. It was not unthinkable."

    old "Sarah began to consider the proposal."
    new "Sarah began to consider the proposal."

    old "The truth was that Maeiv did not have the power to enforce this issue."
    new "The truth was that Maeiv did not have the power to enforce this issue."

    old "If the others disagreed, there would be no single ruler for the Union."
    new "If the others disagreed, there would be no single ruler for the Union."

    old "Then again, perhaps a unified leader was exactly what they needed in a time of impending war."
    new "Then again, perhaps a unified leader was exactly what they needed in a time of impending war."

    old "Sarah tried to play out every scenario in her mind."
    new "Sarah tried to play out every scenario in her mind."

    old "Maeiv. Edmond. Each skilled rulers in their own right."
    new "Maeiv. Edmond. Each skilled rulers in their own right."

    old "Antonio. Sarah shuddered at the idea of such a man having such power."
    new "Antonio. Sarah shuddered at the idea of such a man having such power."

    old "Then, lastly, her mind fall upon herself."
    new "Then, lastly, her mind fall upon herself."

    old "Herself as the Queen of the Union."
    new "Herself as the Queen of the Union."

    old "The idea was at first absurd to her. It was more power than she had ever desired."
    new "The idea was at first absurd to her. It was more power than she had ever desired."

    old "And yet, she found her mind returning to it."
    new "And yet, she found her mind returning to it."

    old "Had she not brought her nation to prosperity while the others languished same as they always did?"
    new "Had she not brought her nation to prosperity while the others languished same as they always did?"

    old "Why not her, then?"
    new "Why not her, then?"

    old "But just as the notion tempted her, she found herself flinching from it."
    new "But just as the notion tempted her, she found herself flinching from it."

    old "So much power...could anyone truly be allowed to wield it? Perhaps none of them should."
    new "So much power...could anyone truly be allowed to wield it? Perhaps none of them should."

    old "Perhaps a council should rule."
    new "Perhaps a council should rule."

    old "Sarah leaned over her desk and uttered a deep sigh."
    new "Sarah leaned over her desk and uttered a deep sigh."

    old "She had to make a decision."
    new "She had to make a decision."

    old "Claim the role for yourself"
    new "Claim the role for yourself"

    old "Sarah knew the answer before she dared to speak it."
    new "Sarah knew the answer before she dared to speak it."

    old "There could be no other but her."
    new "There could be no other but her."

    old "She was the most gifted, and above all, had the best temperament for it."
    new "She was the most gifted, and above all, had the best temperament for it."

    old "Now to convince the others."
    new "Now to convince the others."

    old "Support another"
    new "Support another"

    old "Sarah knew almost instantly that it could not be her."
    new "Sarah knew almost instantly that it could not be her."

    old "They would need a strong leader, she knew that much, but out of all them she had the least experience."
    new "They would need a strong leader, she knew that much, but out of all them she had the least experience."

    old "Then again, there was power in being able to leverage her vote for another."
    new "Then again, there was power in being able to leverage her vote for another."

    old "She had no doubt that the others would all be eager to put themselves up first."
    new "She had no doubt that the others would all be eager to put themselves up first."

    old "She could go into the negotiations, having something to offer rather than something to ask."
    new "She could go into the negotiations, having something to offer rather than something to ask."

    old "Propose a council of rulers"
    new "Propose a council of rulers"

    old "Sarah knew it could not be her."
    new "Sarah knew it could not be her."

    old "In fact, she knew it couldn't be any of them."
    new "In fact, she knew it couldn't be any of them."

    old "Each of them had a weakness to them. A flaw. To raise a single one of them up above the others would only invite disaster."
    new "Each of them had a weakness to them. A flaw. To raise a single one of them up above the others would only invite disaster."

    old "Sarah would have to convince the others to see it the same as her."
    new "Sarah would have to convince the others to see it the same as her."

    old "To understand they would have the rule the Union as a council."
    new "To understand they would have the rule the Union as a council."

